3. Calculate the percentage of long words:
   Long words are words with more than 6 characters. 
   Count the number of long words: 
   (the actual wording and number of long words aren't given here for shorter text and lesser words - use own words and get a basic idea that all non common day to day language terminology is been used and GT-fuel ACSL piezoelect will be part of them)
   53 long words in total 
   Percentage of long words: 53 / 85 x 100% ≈ 62.35%

We use the Swedish LIX formula for the calculation of the readability index.
LIX = (Average words per sentence) + (Average syllables per word x 100 / Average words per sentence) + (Percentage of long words x 100 / 15) - 20 
